ype\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"sed -n '120,160p' GAME_DESIGN.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"## 7. Effect Vocabulary [HARD — the Director's verbs]\\n\\nThe atomic effects from which **all** items, enemy abilities, traps, and shrine-like\\ninteractions are composed. ~16 verbs; each takes bounded parameters. This list is\\nthe single most load-bearing table in the project: the engine implements exactly\\nthese, and the Director's creativity is names + fiction + composition + parameters.\\n\\n| Verb | Parameters (bounds [HARD]) | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| `damage` | amount 1–12 | |\\n| `heal` | amount 1–20 | |\\n| `apply_status` | status (from §6), duration (per §6) | |\\n| `cure_status` | one status or `all` | |\\n| `buff_stat` | ATK or DEF, ±1–3, duration 5–20 | |\\n| `nutrition` | +10–100 Fullness | |\\n| `teleport_self` | random walkable cell | escape valve |\\n| `teleport_target` | random walkable cell | |\\n| `blink` | directed hop 2–4 tiles | |\\n| `knockback` | push 1–3 tiles, collision = 1–3 dmg | |\\n| `reveal` | map / items / enemies / traps (this floor) | |\\n| `identify` | one carried item, or all of one category | |\\n| `enchant` | weapon or armor, +1 (item cap +3) | |\\n| `summon` | 1–3 entities **from this floor's roster**, adjacent cells | no novel entities mid-floor |\\n| `transform` | re-roll target enemy into roster entity of ≤ equal budget cost | |\\n| `dig` | remove wall tiles in a line, length 1–5 | |\\n\\n**Composition rules:** an item or ability bundles **1–3 effects** + one **trigger**\\n+ one **targeting shape**.\\n\\n- Triggers: `quaff`, `read`, `throw_hit`, `equip_passive`, `on_hit` (weapon proc,\\n  chance 10–30% [HARD]), `on_struck` (armor proc, same), `step` (trap), `use`\\n  (tool, 1–5 charges).\\n- Targeting shapes: `self`, `melee`, `bolt` (first target in line, range 3–8),\\n  `burst` (radius 1–2, centered self or impact), `floor`.\\n\\nGrowing this vocabulary is the **intended** post-MVP expansion axis: add a verb to\\nthe engine (with tests), bump the protocol version, and the Director's expressive\\nspace multiplies. Verbs are added by humans via this file, never by the Director.\\n\\n## 8. Items and the Economy\\n\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n./src/engine/run/endings.ts:106:  fallback: RunSummaryFallback = {}\n./src/engine/run/endings.ts:111:  let terminalStatus = fallback.terminalStatus ?? ACTIVE_TERMINAL_STATUS;\n./src/engine/run/endings.ts:112:  let depth = fallback.depth ?? 0;\n./src/engine/run/endings.ts:113:  let turns = fallback.turns ?? 0;\n./phase-plans/PHASE-INDEX.md:47:| 21 | Run loop, caps, win/loss, the Hoard | 17, 20 | 22 | 35m |\n./phase-plans/PHASE-INDEX.md:59:| 26 | Fallback content pack (Old Stock) | 14, 16, 20 | 23–25 | 45m |\n./phase-plans/PHASE-INDEX.md:74:| 36 | Repair loop & fallback degradation | 33, 34, 35 | 37 | 30m |\n./phase-plans/PHASE-INDEX.md:108:| 52 | Floor transition & generation handoff UX | 38, 50 | 53 | 30m |\n./src/harness/fallback-provider.ts:16:  | \"fallback_content_invalid\"\n./src/harness/fallback-provider.ts:17:  | \"fallback_depth_unavailable\";\n./src/harness/fallback-provider.ts:20:  readonly kind = \"fallback-provider-error\";\n./src/harness/fallback-provider.ts:77:      throw wrapProviderError(\"fallback_content_invalid\", null, error);\n./src/harness/fallback-provider.ts:85:        \"fallback_depth_unavailable\",\n./src/harness/fallback-provider.ts:87:        `fallback floor ${depth} is not available`,\n./src/harness/fallback-provider.ts:122:      throw wrapProviderError(\"fallback_content_invalid\", depth, error);\n./src/harness/fallback-provider.ts:137:      ? `fallback content pack is invalid: ${sourceMessage}`\n./src/harness/fallback-provider.ts:138:      : `fallback floor ${depth} is invalid: ${sourceMessage}`;\n./phase-plans/PHASE-59-DEMO-HARDENING.md:4:The NORTH_STAR §6 seven-beat demo runs flawlessly, twice in a row, live.\n./phase-plans/PHASE-59-DEMO-HARDENING.md:7:NORTH_STAR §6 (the